  # Access your PostgreSQL database

%blockquote.info
  :markdown
    You need to have our command line utility
    [Documentation](/cli) - [https://github.com/Scalingo/appsdeck-executables](https://github.com/Scalingo/appsdeck-executables)

:markdown

  ## Use `appsdeck run`

  ```
  appsdeck -a <application name> run -e PGPASSWORD=<password> psql -U <user> -h <host> -p <port> <db>
  ```

  ### Example

  If my application's name is 'example' and it has the environment variable
  `APPSDECK_POSTGRESQL_URL = "postgresql://example_123:H_grwjqBteMMrVye442Zw6@example-123.postgresql.dbs.appsdeck.eu:30000/example_123"`

  You can run:

  ```
  $ appsdeck -a example run -e PGPASSWORD=H_grwjqBteMMrVye442Zw6 psql -U example_123 -h example-123.postgresql.dbs.appsdeck.eu -p 30000 example_123
  psql (9.3.5)
  Type "help" for help.

  example_123=> SELECT version();
                                                 version                                                
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   PostgreSQL 9.3.5 on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu, compiled by gcc (Ubuntu 4.8.2-19ubuntu1) 4.8.2, 64-bit

  ```

